  "decision_conditions": [
    "The rooftop flagpole antenna and associated ducting (to ground floor level  proposed along the front elevation of the building) are considered to create visually obtrusive features which would have a seriously detrimental visual impact on the appearance of this historic building and the Clerkenwall Conservation Area within which it is situated.  The development would therefore fail to comply with  PPS 5 (Planning in the Historic Environment),  policies C17,  D4, D11 and D22 of the Islington’s Unitary Development Plan (2002); policy CS9 of the Islington’s Core Strategy 2011, the Islington Conservation Area Design Guide (2002), Clerkenwell Green Conservation Area Design Guidelines and the Islington Urban Design Guide (2006)."
